    FUNCTION longestPalindrome(s)

        SET f TO a TWO DIMENSIONAL LIST of BOOLEAN TRUES with n ROWS and n COLUMNS

        SET mx TO one  
        FOR i FROM n MINUS two DOWN TO zero  
            FOR j FROM i PLUS one TO n MINUS one  
                SET element at position i and position j of f TO FALSE  
                IF element at position i of s EQUALS element at position j of s  
                    SET element at position i and position j of f TO element at position i PLUS one and position j MINUS one of f  
                    IF element at position i and position j of f EQUALS TRUE AND mx LESS THAN j MINUS i PLUS one  
                        SET k TO i  
                        SET mx TO j MINUS i PLUS one  
                    END IF  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        RETURN substring from position k TO position k PLUS mx MINUS one of s  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

                SET element at position zero j of dp TO the value of element at position zero j MINUS one of dp

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION minCut(s)  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF s  
        IF n LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO one  
            RETURN zero  
        END IF  
        
        SET is_palindrome TO a two dimensional collection of size n by n filled with FALSE  
        
        FOR i FROM zero TO n MINUS one  
            SET element at position i at position i of is_palindrome TO TRUE  
        END FOR  
        
        FOR length FROM two TO n  
            FOR start FROM zero TO n MINUS length  
                SET end TO start PLUS length MINUS one  
                IF length EQUALS two  
                    SET element at position start at position end of is_palindrome TO the condition that element at position start of s EQUALS element at position end of s  
                ELSE  
                    SET element at position start at position end of is_palindrome TO the condition that element at position start of s EQUALS element at position end of s AND the element at position start PLUS one at position end MINUS one of is_palindrome  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        
        SET min_cuts TO a collection of size n filled with zero  
        
        FOR i FROM zero TO n MINUS one  
            IF element at position zero at position i of is_palindrome  
                SET element at position i of min_cuts TO zero  
            ELSE  
                SET element at position i of min_cuts TO positive infinity  
                FOR j FROM one TO i  
                    IF element at position j at position i of is_palindrome AND element at position j MINUS one of min_cuts PLUS one LESS THAN element at position i of min_cuts  
                        SET element at position i of min_cuts TO element at position j MINUS one of min_cuts PLUS one  
                    END IF  
                END FOR  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        
        RETURN element at position n MINUS one of min_cuts  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution
    FUNCTION evalRPN(tokens_of_strings)
        SET stack TO an empty list
        FOR each token IN tokens_of_strings
            IF token IS IN the collection plus minus multiplied by divided by
                SET b TO the element removed FROM the end of stack
                SET a TO the element removed FROM the end of stack
                IF token EQUALS plus
                    APPEND a PLUS b TO stack
                ELSE IF token EQUALS minus
                    APPEND a MINUS b TO stack
                ELSE IF token EQUALS multiplied by
                    APPEND a MULTIPLIED BY b TO stack
                ELSE IF token EQUALS divided by
                    APPEND the integer conversion OF a DIVIDED BY b TO stack
                END IF
            ELSE
                APPEND the integer conversion OF token TO stack
            END IF
        END FOR
        RETURN the element at position zero of stack
    END FUNCTION
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION evalRPN(tokens)  
        SET stack TO an empty list  
        FOR each token IN tokens  
            IF token EQUALS one of the symbols plus MINUS MULTIPLY DIVIDE  
                SET b TO the last element removed from stack  
                SET a TO the last element removed from stack  
                IF token EQUALS plus  
                    APPEND a PLUS b TO stack  
                ELSE IF token EQUALS minus  
                    APPEND a MINUS b TO stack  
                ELSE IF token EQUALS multiply  
                    APPEND a MULTIPLIED BY b TO stack  
                ELSE IF token EQUALS divide  
                    APPEND the integer value of a DIVIDED BY b TO stack  
                END IF  
            ELSE  
                APPEND the integer value of token TO stack  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        RETURN the element at position zero of stack  
    END FUNCTION

                    SET last TO i  
                END IF  
                SET the ELEMENT AT position i OF row c OF prev_occurrence TO last  
            END FOR  
            
            SET last TO minus one  
            FOR i FROM n MINUS one DOWN TO zero  
                IF the ELEMENT AT position i OF s EQUALS char THEN

                END IF  
                SET the ELEMENT AT position i OF row c OF next_occurrence TO last

    FUNCTION validTicTacToe(board)

        END FUNCTION

        SET m TO the LENGTH OF grid_of_strings
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF element at position zero of grid_of_strings
        SET start TO none

            FOR j FROM zero TO n MINUS one
                SET cell TO element at position i of grid_of_strings element at position j
                IF cell EQUALS at symbol
                    SET start TO tuple of i and j
                ELSE IF cell IS LOWERCASE LETTER
                    INCREMENT num_keys BY one
                END IF
            END FOR
        END FOR

        CALL InitializeQueueAndVisited WITH start
        ASSIGN queue TO result of InitializeQueueAndVisited at position zero
        ASSIGN visited TO result of InitializeQueueAndVisited at position one

        WHILE queue IS NOT empty
            CALL PopLeft FROM queue
            ASSIGN x TO result at position zero
            ASSIGN y TO result at position one
            ASSIGN keys TO result at position two
            ASSIGN steps TO result at position three

    FUNCTION movesToStamp(stamp string, target string) RETURNS list of integers  
        SET m TO the LENGTH OF stamp  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF target  
        SET indeg TO a list of size n MINUS m PLUS one where each element is m  
        SET q TO an empty double ended queue

        FOR i FROM zero TO n MINUS m  
            FOR j FROM zero TO m MINUS one  
                SET c TO element at position j of stamp

                    DECREMENT element at position i of indeg BY one

                ELSE

                END IF

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION gridIllumination(n, lamps, queries)  
        SET row_count TO an empty dictionary with default integer zero  
        SET col_count TO an empty dictionary with default integer zero  
        SET diag_count TO an empty dictionary with default integer zero  
        SET anti_diag_count TO an empty dictionary with default integer zero  
        SET lamp_positions TO an empty set  
        
        FOR each pair r c IN the elements of lamps  
            IF the tuple of r and c is not in lamp_positions  
                ADD the tuple of r and c TO lamp_positions  
                INCREMENT the value at key r in row_count BY one  
                INCREMENT the value at key c in col_count BY one  
                INCREMENT the value at key the subtraction of c from r in diag_count BY one  
                INCREMENT the value at key the sum of r and c in anti_diag_count BY one  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        
        SET directions TO the list of pairs negative one negative one negative one zero negative one one zero negative one zero zero zero zero one one negative one one zero one one one  
        
        SET result TO an empty list  
        
        FOR each pair r c IN the elements of queries  
            IF the value at key r in row_count is greater than zero OR the value at key c in col_count is greater than zero OR the value at key the subtraction of c from r in diag_count is greater than zero OR the value at key the sum of r and c in anti_diag_count is greater than zero  
                APPEND one TO result  
            ELSE  
                APPEND zero TO result  
            END IF

                    DECREMENT the value at key the sum of nr and nc in anti_diag_count BY one  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  
        
        RETURN result  
    END FUNCTION

CLASS Solution
    FUNCTION canConvert(input_string_one, input_string_two)
        IF input_string_one EQUALS input_string_two
            RETURN true
        END IF

        SET conversion_map TO empty mapping

        FOR each pair of character_one AND character_two IN corresponding positions OF input_string_one AND input_string_two

                IF the value at character_one IN conversion_map NOT EQUALS character_two
                    RETURN false
                END IF
            ELSE
                SET the value at character_one IN conversion_map TO character_two
            END IF
        END FOR

        IF the LENGTH OF the set OF characters OF input_string_two EQUALS twenty six
            RETURN false
        END IF

        RETURN true
    END FUNCTION
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION cherryPickup(grid)  
        SET rows TO the LENGTH OF grid  
        SET cols TO the LENGTH OF element at position zero of grid

                END FOR

        END FUNCTION  
        
        RETURN dp(zero zero cols MINUS one)

        SET g_cat TO a list containing an empty list FOR EACH element FROM zero TO m MULTIPLIED BY n MINUS one

                    CONTINUE to the next iteration  
                END IF

                ELSE IF character c EQUALS the character M

                ELSE IF character c EQUALS the character F  
                    SET food TO v

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION deleteDuplicateFolder(self, paths)  
        SET ans TO an empty list  
        SET root TO a new TrieNode object  
        SET subtreeToNodes TO a new default dictionary with list as default value  

        FOR each path IN the sorted order of paths  
            SET node TO root  
            FOR each s IN path  
                SET node TO the child node of node.children corresponding to the element s  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  

        FUNCTION buildSubtreeToRoots(node)

                the concatenation FOR each s IN the children of node OF  
                    the element s concatenated WITH buildSubtreeToRoots called with the child node corresponding to s  
                AND THEN a closing parenthesis  
            IF subtree NOT EQUALS the string consisting of opening and closing parenthesis with nothing in between  
                APPEND node TO the list in subtreeToNodes corresponding to the key subtree  
            END IF  
            RETURN subtree  
        END FUNCTION  

        CALL buildSubtreeToRoots with root as argument  

        FOR each nodes IN the values of subtreeToNodes  
            IF the length of nodes GREATER THAN one  
                FOR each node IN nodes  
                    SET node.deleted TO True  
                END FOR

        CALL constructPath with root and an empty list as arguments

class UnionFind:
  init(size): parent=[0..size-1], rank=[1]*size
  find(p): if parent[p]!=p: parent[p]=find(parent[p]); return parent[p]
  union(p,q):
    rp=find(p); rq=find(q)
    if rp==rq: return False
    if rank[rp]>rank[rq]: parent[rq]=rp
    else if rank[rp]<rank[rq]: parent[rp]=rq
    else: parent[rq]=rp; rank[rp]+=1
    return True

gcdSort(nums):
  sorted_nums=sorted(nums)
  max_val=max(nums)
  uf=UnionFind(max_val+1)
  for num in nums:
    for f in 2..sqrt(num):
      if num%f==0: uf.union(num,f); uf.union(num,num//f)
  for i in 0..len(nums)-1:
    if uf.find(nums[i]) != uf.find(sorted_nums[i]): return False
  return True

CLASS UnionFind  
    FUNCTION __init__(self, size)  
        SET self.parent TO list of integers from zero TO size MINUS one  
        SET self.rank TO list containing size copies of one  
    END FUNCTION  

    FUNCTION find(self, p)  
        IF element at position p of self.parent NOT EQUALS p  
            SET element at position p of self.parent TO self.find(element at position p of self.parent)  
        END IF  
        RETURN element at position p of self.parent  
    END FUNCTION  

    FUNCTION union(self, p, q)  
        SET rootP TO self.find(p)  
        SET rootQ TO self.find(q)  
        IF rootP EQUALS rootQ  
            RETURN False  
        END IF  
        IF element at position rootP of self.rank GREATER THAN element at position rootQ of self.rank  
            SET element at position rootQ of self.parent TO rootP  
        ELSE IF element at position rootP of self.rank LESS THAN element at position rootQ of self.rank  
            SET element at position rootP of self.parent TO rootQ  
        ELSE  
            SET element at position rootQ of self.parent TO rootP  
            INCREMENT element at position rootP of self.rank BY one  
        END IF  
        RETURN True  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS  

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION gcdSort(self, nums)  
        SET sorted_nums TO nums sorted in ascending order  
        SET max_val TO the maximum value in nums  
        SET uf TO a new UnionFind object initialized with max_val PLUS one  

        FOR each num IN nums  
            FOR each factor FROM two TO the integer part of the square root of num PLUS one  
                IF num MODULO factor EQUALS zero  
                    CALL uf.union(num, factor)  
                    CALL uf.union(num, num DIVIDED BY factor)  
                END IF  
            END FOR  
        END FOR  

        FOR each i FROM zero TO the length of nums MINUS one  
            IF uf.find(element at position i of nums) NOT EQUALS uf.find(element at position i of sorted_nums)  
                RETURN False  
            END IF  
        END FOR  

        RETURN True  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

CLASS Solution
    FUNCTION minimumFinishTime(tires, changeTime, numLaps)
        SET min_times TO a list of length FIFTEEN with all elements set to positive infinity
        FOR each pair of first_variable AND ratio IN tires
            SET total_time TO zero
            FOR index FROM zero TO FOURTEEN
                SET lap_time TO first_variable MULTIPLIED BY ratio RAISED TO the power of index
                IF lap_time IS GREATER THAN changeTime PLUS first_variable
                    BREAK the current loop
                END IF
                SET total_time TO total_time PLUS lap_time
                IF total_time IS LESS THAN element at position index of min_times
                    SET element at position index of min_times TO total_time
                END IF
            END FOR
        END FOR

        SET dp TO a list of length numLaps PLUS one with all elements set to positive infinity
        SET element at position zero of dp TO zero

        FOR i FROM one TO numLaps
            FOR j FROM zero TO THE LESSER OF i MINUS one AND FOURTEEN
                SET candidate_time TO element at position i MINUS j MINUS one of dp PLUS element at position j of min_times PLUS changeTime
                IF candidate_time IS LESS THAN element at position i of dp
                    SET element at position i of dp TO candidate_time
                END IF
            END FOR
        END FOR

        RETURN element at position numLaps of dp MINUS changeTime
    END FUNCTION
END CLASS

CLASS Solution  
    FUNCTION maximumBeauty(flowers newFlowers target full partial)  
        CALL flowers SORT IN ASCENDING ORDER  
        SET n TO the LENGTH OF flowers  
        SET max_beauty TO zero  
        SET prefix_sum TO A LIST OF ZEROS WITH LENGTH n PLUS one  
        FOR i FROM zero TO n MINUS one  
            SET element at POSITION i PLUS one OF prefix_sum TO element at POSITION i OF prefix_sum PLUS element at POSITION i OF flowers  
        END FOR  
        SET complete_gardens TO zero  
        FOR i FROM n MINUS one DOWN TO zero  
            IF element at POSITION i OF flowers GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO target THEN  
                INCREMENT complete_gardens BY one  
            ELSE  
                BREAK  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        SET remaining_flowers TO newFlowers  
        SET max_incomplete_flowers TO zero  
        FOR i FROM complete_gardens TO n  
            IF i GREATER THAN zero THEN  
                DECREMENT remaining_flowers BY target MINUS element at POSITION n MINUS i OF flowers  
                IF remaining_flowers LESS THAN zero THEN  
                    BREAK  
                END IF  
            END IF  
            SET left TO zero  
            SET right TO n MINUS i MINUS one  
            WHILE left LESS THAN OR EQUAL TO right  
                SET mid TO left PLUS right DIVIDED BY two USING INTEGER DIVISION  
                SET cost TO element at POSITION mid OF flowers MULTIPLIED BY mid PLUS one MINUS element at POSITION mid PLUS one OF prefix_sum  
                IF cost GREATER THAN remaining_flowers THEN  
                    DECREMENT right BY one PLUS mid MINUS right  
                ELSE  
                    INCREMENT left BY one PLUS mid MINUS left  
                END IF  
            END WHILE  
            IF right GREATER THAN OR EQUAL TO zero THEN  
                SET max_incomplete_flowers TO element at POSITION right OF flowers PLUS remaining_flowers MINUS element at POSITION right OF flowers MULTIPLIED BY right PLUS one PLUS NEGATION OF element at POSITION right PLUS one OF prefix_sum DIVIDED BY right PLUS one USING INTEGER DIVISION  
            ELSE  
                SET max_incomplete_flowers TO zero  
            END IF  
            SET total_beauty TO i MULTIPLIED BY full PLUS THE MINIMUM OF max_incomplete_flowers AND target MINUS one MULTIPLIED BY partial  
            IF total_beauty GREATER THAN max_beauty THEN  
                SET max_beauty TO total_beauty  
            END IF  
        END FOR  
        RETURN max_beauty  
    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS

                RETURN

        FOR start_city FROM zero TO n MINUS one  
            SET visited TO a set containing start_city  
            CALL dfs WITH start_city visited zero zero  
        END FOR

    END FUNCTION  
END CLASS
